---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import FAQ from '../../../components/FAQ.astro';
import ServiceSchema from '../../../components/ServiceSchema.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Swimming Pools | Construction, Maintenance & Equipment"
  description="Custom pool construction, renovation, and maintenance services. Filtration systems, equipment installation, and expert pool care in Valencia, San Diego and Caracas."
  image="/images/piscinas.webp"
  activePage="services"
>
  <header class="article-hero">
    <div class="hero-bg" style="background-image: url('/images/piscinas.webp')"></div>
    <div class="hero-overlay"></div>
    <div class="hero-content">
      <a href="/en/services" class="back-link">← Back to Services</a>
      <span class="article-category">Outdoor Living</span>
      <h1 class="article-title"><span class="line">Swimming</span><span class="line gold">Pools</span></h1>
      <p class="article-excerpt">Custom pool construction, renovation, and maintenance for Venezuelan properties.</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="article-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="article-body">
        <p>A swimming pool is more than just a place to cool off—it's a lifestyle investment that transforms your outdoor space into a personal retreat. Whether you're building a new pool, renovating an existing one, or need professional maintenance, ReformaT Venezuela delivers expert service with European standards.</p>

        <img src="/images/piscinas.webp" alt="Custom swimming pool by ReformaT Venezuela" loading="eager" fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" />

        <h2>Custom Pool Construction</h2>

        <p>We design and build custom pools that complement your property's architecture and your lifestyle. Our construction process includes:</p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Design consultation:</strong> Understanding your vision, space constraints, and budget</li>
          <li><strong>3D visualization:</strong> Photorealistic renders showing exactly how your pool will look</li>
          <li><strong>Engineering:</strong> Structural calculations and soil analysis for safe, lasting construction</li>
          <li><strong>Permitting:</strong> Handling all required approvals and inspections</li>
          <li><strong>Construction:</strong> Excavation, steel reinforcement, plumbing, electrical, shotcrete/gunite application, and finishing</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Pool Types We Build</h2>

        <p><strong>Concrete Pools:</strong> The most customizable option. Shotcrete or gunite construction allows any shape, size, or depth. Finished with plaster, quartz, or pebble surfaces in dozens of colors.</p>

        <p><strong>Infinity Edge Pools:</strong> Dramatic vanishing edge designs that create the illusion of water extending to the horizon. Perfect for properties with views.</p>

        <p><strong>Lap Pools:</strong> Long, narrow pools designed for swimming exercise. Ideal for narrow lots or fitness-focused homeowners.</p>

        <p><strong>Plunge Pools:</strong> Compact pools for cooling off and relaxation. Require less space, water, and maintenance than full-size pools.</p>

        <h2>Pool Renovation & Remodeling</h2>

        <p>If your existing pool is showing its age, we can transform it into a modern oasis:</p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Resurfacing:</strong> Replacing old plaster with modern quartz or pebble finishes</li>
          <li><strong>Tile replacement:</strong> Updating waterline tile with contemporary designs</li>
          <li><strong>Equipment upgrades:</strong> Installing energy-efficient pumps, filters, and heaters</li>
          <li><strong>Lighting upgrades:</strong> LED lighting systems with color-changing options</li>
          <li><strong>Feature additions:</strong> Waterfalls, fountains, bubblers, and spa additions</li>
          <li><strong>Deck replacement:</strong> New coping and deck surfaces in travertine, porcelain, or stamped concrete</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Filtration & Circulation Systems</h2>

        <p>Proper filtration is the heart of a healthy pool. We install and maintain state-of-the-art systems:</p>

        <p><strong>Variable-Speed Pumps:</strong> Energy-efficient pumps that use up to 80% less electricity than single-speed models. They run at lower speeds for longer periods, providing better filtration and quieter operation.</p>

        <p><strong>Cartridge Filters:</strong> Easy to maintain and provide excellent water clarity. No backwashing required, saving thousands of gallons of water annually.</p>

        <p><strong>Sand Filters:</strong> Traditional, reliable filtration with simple maintenance. Ideal for larger pools.</p>

        <p><strong>DE Filters:</strong> Diatomaceous earth filters provide the finest filtration, removing particles down to 2-5 microns.</p>

        <h2>Sanitation Systems</h2>

        <p>Beyond traditional chlorine, we install modern sanitation options:</p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Salt Water Systems:</strong> Generate chlorine from salt, providing softer water with less eye and skin irritation</li>
          <li><strong>UV Systems:</strong> Ultraviolet light destroys bacteria and viruses, reducing chemical needs</li>
          <li><strong>Ozone Systems:</strong> Powerful oxidation that breaks down contaminants</li>
          <li><strong>Mineral Systems:</strong> Silver and copper ions provide natural sanitization</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Pool Automation & Smart Features</h2>

        <p>Modern pools can be controlled from your smartphone:</p>

        <ul>
          <li>Remote control of pumps, heaters, and lighting</li>
          <li>Automated cleaning schedules</li>
          <li>Temperature monitoring and adjustment</li>
          <li>Chemical level monitoring</li>
          <li>Integration with home automation systems</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Maintenance Services</h2>

        <p>Regular maintenance keeps your pool crystal clear and equipment running efficiently:</p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Weekly service:</strong> Skimming, vacuuming, brushing, chemical balancing, and equipment inspection</li>
          <li><strong>Monthly deep cleaning:</strong> Filter cleaning, tile scrubbing, and detailed equipment maintenance</li>
          <li><strong>Seasonal opening/closing:</strong> Preparing pools for heavy use or extended periods of non-use</li>
          <li><strong>Emergency repairs:</strong> Quick response to equipment failures, leaks, or water quality issues</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Energy Efficiency</h2>

        <p>Pools can be significant energy consumers. We help reduce operating costs:</p>

        <ul>
          <li>Variable-speed pumps that save up to 80% on electricity</li>
          <li>LED lighting that uses 85% less energy than incandescent bulbs</li>
          <li>Solar heating options to extend swimming season</li>
          <li>Pool covers that reduce heat loss and evaporation</li>
          <li>Timer systems that run equipment only when needed</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Why Choose ReformaT for Pool Services?</h2>

        <ul>
          <li>Experienced pool builders and technicians</li>
          <li>Custom design with 3D visualization</li>
          <li>Energy-efficient equipment options</li>
          <li>Modern sanitation systems beyond chlorine</li>
          <li>Smart automation integration</li>
          <li>Comprehensive maintenance programs</li>
          <li>Warranties on all construction and equipment</li>
          <li>English-speaking project management available</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Ready to build or renovate your pool?</strong> <a href="/en/contact">Schedule your free consultation</a> and start planning your backyard oasis.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-section">
    <div class="cta-wrapper">
      <h2 class="cta-title">Ready for Your Dream Pool?</h2>
      <p class="cta-text">Schedule a free consultation and receive a detailed pool construction or renovation proposal.</p>
      <a href="/en/contact" class="btn-premium btn-primary-premium">
        <span class="btn-content">Request a Quote</span>
        <span class="btn-border"></span>
        <span class="btn-shine"></span>
        <span class="btn-arrow">→</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Service",
  "name": "Swimming Pools",
  "description": "Pool construction, renovation and maintenance with modern filtration systems in Venezuela.",
  "url": "https://reformatvenezuela.com/en/services/pools",
  "provider": {
    "@type": "HomeAndConstructionBusiness",
    "name": "ReformaT Venezuela",
    "url": "https://reformatvenezuela.com"
  },
  "areaServed": [
    {
      "@type": "City",
      "name": "Valencia"
    },
    {
      "@type": "City",
      "name": "San Diego"
    },
    {
      "@type": "City",
      "name": "Caracas"
    },
    {
      "@type": "City",
      "name": "La Guaira"
    }
  ]
}
</script>

  <ServiceSchema
    name="Pool Construction"
    description="Residential pool design and construction"
    serviceType="Pool Construction"
  />
</BaseLayout>


<FAQ title="Frequently Asked Questions" items={[
  { question: "Do you build custom pools?", answer: "Yes, we design and build custom pools tailored to your space, preferences, and budget. From modern infinity pools to traditional designs." },
  { question: "What maintenance services do you offer?", answer: "We provide weekly and monthly maintenance including cleaning, chemical balancing, filter maintenance, equipment checks, and seasonal preparations." },
  { question: "Can you renovate an existing pool?", answer: "Absolutely. We renovate pools with new tiles, updated equipment, modern finishes, lighting upgrades, and structural repairs to restore your pool to like-new condition." },
  { question: "How long does pool construction take?", answer: "Building a new pool takes between 4 and 8 weeks, depending on size, terrain complexity, and selected finishes." }
]} />

<style>
  .article-hero { position: relative; min-height: 80vh; display: flex; align-items: flex-end; justify-content: center; text-align: center; color: var(--white); overflow: hidden; padding-top: 140px; padding-bottom: 80px; }
  .hero-bg { position: absolute; inset: 0; background-size: cover; background-position: center; z-index: 1; }
  .hero-overlay { position: absolute; inset: 0; background: linear-gradient(to top, rgba(0,0,0,0.95) 0%, rgba(0,0,0,0.4) 60%, rgba(0,0,0,0.2) 100%); z-index: 2; }
  .hero-content { position: relative; z-index: 3; max-width: 900px; padding: 0 20px; }
  .article-category { display: inline-block; background: rgba(201,169,97,0.2); border: 1px solid var(--gold); color: var(--gold); padding: 8px 20px; border-radius: 30px; font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 2px; margin-bottom: 25px; backdrop-filter: blur(10px); }
  .article-title { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 5rem); font-weight: 400; margin-bottom: 20px; line-height: 1.1; }
  .article-title .line { display: block; }
  .article-excerpt { font-size: 1.3rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); max-width: 700px; margin: 0 auto; line-height: 1.6; font-weight: 400; }
  .back-link { display: inline-block; color: var(--gold); font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 20px; transition: 0.3s; text-decoration: none; }
  .article-section { padding: 80px 0; background: var(--white); }
  .article-body { max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.3rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--text); }
  .article-body h2 { font-size: 2.5rem; margin: 3rem 0 1.5rem; color: var(--text); line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 500; }
  .article-body h3 { font-size: 1.8rem; margin: 2.5rem 0 1rem; color: var(--text); font-weight: 500; }
  .article-body p { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; font-weight: 400; }
  .article-body a { color: var(--gold); text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gold); }
  .article-body ul, .article-body ol { margin: 1.5rem 0 1.5rem 2rem; }
  .article-body li { margin-bottom: 0.75rem; font-weight: 400; }
  .article-body img { border-radius: 12px; margin: 2.5rem 0; box-shadow: 0 15px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.08); width: 100%; }
  .article-body > p:first-of-type::first-letter { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 4.5rem; font-weight: 600; float: left; line-height: 0.75; margin-right: 0.15em; color: var(--gold); margin-top: 8px; }
  .cta-section { background: var(--bg); color: var(--white); text-align: center; padding: 110px 24px; width: 100%; }
  .cta-wrapper { max-width: 950px; margin: 0 auto; display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; }
  .cta-title { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 5vw, 3.6rem); font-weight: 400; margin-bottom: 24px; line-height: 1.15; color: var(--white); }
  .cta-text { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.85); max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto 45px; font-size: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.7; }
  .cta-section .btn-premium { padding: 20px 55px; font-size: 0.9rem; }
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .article-hero { min-height: 70vh; padding-top: 120px; padding-bottom: 60px; }
    .article-title { font-size: clamp(2rem, 8vw, 3.5rem); }
    .article-excerpt { font-size: 1.15rem; }
    .article-body { font-size: 1.15rem; }
    .article-body h2 { font-size: 2rem; }
    .article-body h3 { font-size: 1.5rem; }
    .cta-section { padding: 90px 20px; }
  }
</style>